<PageTitle>SymbolLabsForge - Musical Symbol Testing Platform</PageTitle>

<h1>Welcome to SymbolLabsForge</h1>

<div class="welcome-container">
    <div class="intro-section">
        <p class="lead">
            <strong>SymbolLabsForge</strong> is an educational platform for testing and generating musical symbols
            with visual regression testing capabilities.
        </p>
        <p>
            This platform demonstrates real-world software testing concepts through interactive comparison
            workflows and synthetic symbol generation - perfect for undergraduate and graduate coursework
            in computer graphics, image processing, and software quality assurance.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="tools-grid">
        <div class="tool-card">
            <h2>🔍 Symbol Comparison</h2>
            <p>
                Upload your musical symbols (sharp, flat, natural, treble clef) and compare them against
                canonical reference outputs.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Visual diff generation (red highlights show differences)</li>
                <li>Tolerance-based comparison (0.0% to 10.0%)</li>
                <li>Statistical similarity metrics</li>
                <li>Pass/fail validation with detailed feedback</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/comparison" class="btn btn-primary">Start Comparison →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="tool-card">
            <h2>🎨 Symbol Generator</h2>
            <p>
                Generate synthetic musical symbols with precise control over size and rendering parameters.
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>5 symbol types (Sharp, Flat, Natural, Double Sharp, Treble Clef)</li>
                <li>Customizable dimensions (10×10 to 500×1000 pixels)</li>
                <li>Aspect ratio validation and DoS prevention</li>
                <li>Download as PNG or use directly in comparison workflow</li>
            </ul>
            <a href="/generator" class="btn btn-primary">Generate Symbols →</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="learning-objectives">
        <h2>Learning Objectives</h2>
        <div class="audience-tiers">
            <div class="tier">
                <h3>Undergraduate Level</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Understanding visual regression testing concepts</li>
                    <li>Pixel-by-pixel image comparison algorithms</li>
                    <li>Tolerance-based validation strategies</li>
                    <li>File upload and form validation in web applications</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tier">
                <h3>Graduate Level</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Service layer architecture and dependency injection</li>
                    <li>Memory caching strategies for performance optimization</li>
                    <li>Comprehensive error handling and user feedback patterns</li>
                    <li>DoS prevention through input validation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tier">
                <h3>PhD / Research Level</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Adaptive parameter recommendation systems</li>
                    <li>ML-guided symbol generation optimization</li>
                    <li>Statistical similarity metrics and threshold tuning</li>
                    <li>Reproducible experiment design for computer vision</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="getting-started">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <strong>Option 1: Generate a Symbol</strong>
                <p>Visit the <a href="/generator">Symbol Generator</a> to create a synthetic musical symbol
                with your desired parameters.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Option 2: Upload Your Symbol</strong>
                <p>If you already have a symbol image (PNG or JPG), go directly to
                <a href="/comparison">Symbol Comparison</a>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Compare Against Canonical</strong>
                <p>Select the symbol type (Sharp, Flat, Natural, etc.) and adjust the tolerance threshold
                to see how your symbol compares.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Review Results</strong>
                <p>View detailed statistics, visual diff images, and pass/fail status with actionable feedback.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="technical-details">
        <h2>Technical Architecture</h2>
        <p>
            Built with <strong>Blazor Server (.NET 9.0)</strong>, this platform demonstrates:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Phase 9.1 Integration:</strong> SnapshotComparer and ImageDiffGenerator utilities</li>
            <li><strong>Phase 10.1:</strong> Service layer architecture (ComparisonService, SymbolGenerationService)</li>
            <li><strong>Phase 10.2:</strong> Generator integration with memory caching</li>
            <li><strong>Phase 10.3:</strong> Interactive Blazor components with teaching overlays</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-muted">
            <em>See project documentation for detailed implementation notes, teaching artifacts,
            and governance protocols.</em>
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
